p: Table 9 compares ADC of nutrients, gross energy, essential amino acids and fatty acids across diets. We did not find significant differences between diets for the ADC of Crude protein (ranges from 68% to 71%), lipid (ranges from), and energy (ranges from 78 to 79%). The ADC of ash was significantly higher in the N. oculata co-product diet (43.2%) than in the N. oculata whole cells diet (27%), but reference (37.2%) and N. oculata co-product diet did not show any differences ( Table 9).
